slbCurCfgUrlRedirNonGetOrigSrv.name: slbCurCfgUrlRedirNonGetOrigSrv
slbCurCfgUrlRedirNonGetOrigSrv.description: This is for controlling if the switch should redirect packet to the origin server when HTTP non-GETs are detected. enabled(1) - Allow redirect traffic to the origin server disabled(2)- redirect to a group of servers

slbNewCfgUrlLbPathDelete.description: Action object to delete an URL Path. When set to the value of 2 (delete), the entire row is deleted. When read, other(1) is returned. Setting the value to anything other than delete(2) has no effect on the state of the row.
